subSubSection.paragraph:
Discussion : Previous morphological descriptions based on material from Italy (
Brölemann 1889
), Mexico (
Silvestri 1909
) and Palestine (
Negrea & Matic 1996
) apply to specimens from Australia , Argentina and the Democratic Republic of Congo . Particularly distinctive characters are the complete absence of ocelli, 24 antennal articles with the series of articles distal to article 4 being of similar size and shape (
Figs. 1, 2
) (versus shortened articles in pairs alternating with groups of longer articles in other species of
Lamyctes
), the dental margin of the maxillipede having two true teeth, a median swelling, and a conical, seta­like pseudoporodont (
Figs. 3, 4
), and distal spinose projections on the tibiae confined to legs 1­11 .
